00:00.000 --> 00:02.160
Do you need to re-energize a
00:02.160 --> 00:04.430
lesson so you can engage your
00:04.430 --> 00:06.530
students? Consider the ENGAGE
00:06.530 --> 00:08.520
method. What do you normally do
00:08.520 --> 00:10.440
during your day one syllabus
00:10.440 --> 00:12.680
lessons semester after semester
00:12.680 --> 00:15.000
? After you apply the ENGAGE
00:15.000 --> 00:17.000
steps, your lesson will...
00:17.000 --> 00:19.070
Step one, energize. Prepare
00:19.070 --> 00:21.170
your students for learning.
00:21.170 --> 00:23.400
Step two, navigate content. You
00:23.400 --> 00:25.340
can enable high level student
00:25.340 --> 00:27.660
learning. Step three, generate
00:27.660 --> 00:29.740
meaning and involve students in
00:29.740 --> 00:32.000
their own learning process.
00:32.000 --> 00:34.590
Step four, apply to the real
00:34.590 --> 00:37.030
world and possibly showcase
00:37.030 --> 00:39.000
student learning.
00:39.000 --> 00:40.840
Step five, you want to gauge
00:40.840 --> 00:42.600
and celebrate. How can we
00:42.600 --> 00:44.900
encourage meaningful learning?
00:44.900 --> 00:47.120
And the last step, six, we want
00:47.120 --> 00:48.730
to extend that learning and
00:48.730 --> 00:50.000
make it active.
00:50.000 --> 00:51.740
The best way to interact with
00:51.740 --> 00:53.470
this tutorial is to download
00:53.470 --> 00:55.520
the Associated Lesson Worksheet
00:55.520 --> 00:57.290
and note any changes you would
00:57.290 --> 00:59.100
like to make as we explore each
00:59.100 --> 01:00.750
step together. Which new
01:00.750 --> 01:02.720
strategies would work with your
01:02.720 --> 01:04.580
students? I'm sure you'll be
01:04.580 --> 01:06.170
using a few CATS classroom
01:06.170 --> 01:08.200
assessment techniques, but you
01:08.200 --> 01:10.180
may find graphic organizers are
01:10.180 --> 01:12.000
quite helpful as well.
01:12.000 --> 01:13.750
Be sure to select strategies
01:13.750 --> 01:15.730
that address the learning needs
01:15.730 --> 01:17.840
and interests of your students.
01:17.840 --> 01:19.590
If you need TNLC assistance
01:19.590 --> 01:20.910
with more complicated
01:20.910 --> 01:22.080
strategies such as
01:22.080 --> 01:24.140
collaborative group projects,
01:24.140 --> 01:25.700
be sure to reach out to any
01:25.700 --> 01:28.000
